":25503,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/bismillah-begin-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":28901,"position":0},"title":"Hadith on Bismillah: Reciting name of Allah to begin prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them, would open the prayer by reciting, \u201cAll praise is due to Allah.\u201d (1:1) In the narration of Muslim, Anas said: I did not hear any of them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37577,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/12\/19\/umar-tarak-salah\/","url_meta":{"origin":28901,"position":1},"title":"Umar on Salat: No share of Islam for one who leaves prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 19, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Al-Miswar ibn Makhramah reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cThere is no share of Islam for one who abandons the prayer.\u201d Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a' 117 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u0645\u0650\u0633\u0652\u0648\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0645\u064e\u062e\u0652\u0631\u064e\u0645\u064e\u0629\u064e \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631 \u0628\u0652\u0646 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u0651\u064e\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u064e\u0636\u0650\u064a\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u0647\u064f \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u062d\u064e\u0638\u0651\u064e \u0641\u0650\u064a\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37419,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/11\/23\/taqsir-salat-security\/","url_meta":{"origin":28901,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Shortening prayer in times of safety","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 23, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Ya\u2019la ibn Umayyah reported: I said to Umar ibn al-Khattab about the verse, \u201cThere is no blame upon you for shortening the prayer if you fear persecution from those who disbelieve,\u201d (4:101). I said, \u201cThe people are now safe.\u201d Umar said, \u201cI wondered about it as you did, so I\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Quran Exegesis \u0627\u0644\u062a\u0641\u0633\u064a\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/quran-exegesis-tafsir\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":43679,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/05\/14\/prophet-always-with-abu-bakr-umar\/","url_meta":{"origin":28901,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Caliphs: The Prophet always with Abu Bakr and Umar","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 14, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Abbas reported: Umar was placed upon his bier as the people surrounded him, supplicated for him, and performed the funeral prayer over him before he was taken away. I was there, and nothing else held my attention but a man putting his hand on my shoulder. It was Ali,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25415,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/11\/13\/salat-shortened-two-rakaat-travel\/","url_meta":{"origin":28901,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Travel: Prayer shortened to two cycles during travel","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 13, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: I accompanied the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, and during travel he would not add more to his prayer than two cycles. Abu Bakr, Umar, and Uthman did likewise, may Allah be pleased with them. Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 1051, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 689 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":13893,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/05\/02\/no-salat-bathroom\/","url_meta":{"origin":28901,"position":5},"title":"Umar on Salat: No praying if you need to relieve yourself","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 2, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Zayd ibn Aslam reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cLet not one of you pray while holding his bowels.\u201d Source: al-Muwat\u0323t\u0323a' 381 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0632\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0644\u064e\u0645\u064e \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0639\u064f\u0645\u064e\u0631\u064e \u0628\u0652\u0646\u064e \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062e\u064e\u0637\u064e\u0651\u0627\u0628\u0650 \u0631\u0636\u064a \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0639\u0646\u0647 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0644\u064e\u0627 \u064a\u064f\u0635\u064e\u0644\u0650\u0651\u064a\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0623\u064e\u062d